Michael Wierzbicki, Gene Pekarik
A meta-analysis was conducted of 125 studies on psychotherapy dropout. Mean dropout rate was 46.86%. Dropout rate was unrelated to most of the variables that were examined but differed significantly as a function of definition of dropout.
